1
00:02:18,005 --> 00:02:20,171
What are spirits?

2
00:02:20,255 --> 00:02:22,005
What? Why are you asking that now?

3
00:02:22,463 --> 00:02:26,546
Yesterday, I heard our neighbor's
grandma telling my mom.

4
00:02:26,588 --> 00:02:29,796
A girl they knew hung herself and died.

5
00:02:29,963 --> 00:02:36,213
Later, that girl's spirit possessed her friend,
and she also hung herself and died.

6
00:02:36,755 --> 00:02:38,421
Do spirits really exist?

7
00:02:38,755 --> 00:02:40,296
That's all nonsense.

8
00:02:40,338 --> 00:02:44,171
These old people have nothing
better to do at home,

9
00:02:44,171 --> 00:02:48,005
so they go around gossiping
about such things from house to house.

10
00:02:48,046 --> 00:02:50,421
Don't even think about it.

11
00:02:50,463 --> 00:02:52,421
Spirits and all that are just trash.

12
00:02:52,713 --> 00:02:55,130
But I'm really scared.

13
00:02:55,130 --> 00:02:56,171
Boo!

14
00:06:17,963 --> 00:06:19,671
Oh my god...

15
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:21,255
Why are you crying?

16
00:06:21,546 --> 00:06:23,505
We have entrusted her to that Swamiji, right?

17
00:06:23,671 --> 00:06:25,713
He is no ordinary person.

18
00:06:25,796 --> 00:06:30,130
He is a great man who has crushed
even the most powerful evil spirits under his feet.

19
00:06:30,713 --> 00:06:35,880
It's the girl's good fortune that you got to know
about this great man through me.

20
00:06:36,255 --> 00:06:37,421
Don't worry.

21
00:06:37,963 --> 00:06:39,880
The girl will definitely get well.

22
00:06:40,796 --> 00:06:42,921
There he is... Swamiji! Swamiji!

23
00:06:43,130 --> 00:06:44,463
What timing you have, Swamiji?

24
00:06:45,838 --> 00:06:48,838
Swamiji, slowly, slowly. Please come in, Swamiji.

25
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:49,630
Swami!

26
00:06:51,421 --> 00:06:53,171
Which grave did she go to this time?

27
00:06:53,463 --> 00:06:55,130
Muniyamma, from the next village.

28
00:06:55,671 --> 00:06:57,796
She burned herself to death ten days ago.

29
00:06:58,505 --> 00:07:00,380
She went and slept near that grave.

30
00:07:05,213 --> 00:07:08,296
Changing graves every day,
is she trying to change me?

31
00:07:09,463 --> 00:07:10,421
I'll teach her a lesson.

32
00:07:41,463 --> 00:07:42,630
What is this?

33
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:45,588
Are you playing games with me?

34
00:07:48,005 --> 00:07:50,838
Are you trying to deceive and send me away?

35
00:07:55,255 --> 00:07:57,505
Do you think I can't find out who you are?

36
00:08:00,838 --> 00:08:01,880
This won't work!

37
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:04,213
Swami!

38
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:06,380
Oh my god!

39
00:08:07,213 --> 00:08:07,838
Hey!

40
00:08:09,005 --> 00:08:10,505
How much longer will you stay here?

41
00:08:11,463 --> 00:08:13,171
Will you leave this girl or not?

42
00:08:16,171 --> 00:08:17,296
Swami!

43
00:08:18,130 --> 00:08:18,713
Don't hit me!

44
00:08:24,005 --> 00:08:26,796
She's just a child, Swami! She will die!
Don't hit her!

45
00:08:28,588 --> 00:08:29,713
Nothing will happen!

46
00:08:31,088 --> 00:08:34,171
If you are patient now,
the spirit possessing her will leave.

47
00:08:35,005 --> 00:08:36,921
Otherwise, you all will die!

48
00:08:40,463 --> 00:08:43,838
Until you go back to your grave,
this will be your punishment!

49
00:08:46,088 --> 00:08:48,963
(Chanting)

50
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:56,255
(Chanting)

51
00:09:16,213 --> 00:09:17,255
My dear!

52
00:09:20,630 --> 00:09:22,338
My dear!

53
00:09:33,171 --> 00:09:33,963
My dear!

54
00:09:36,921 --> 00:09:38,796
Get up, dear.

55
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:40,505
Naina!

56
00:11:40,880 --> 00:11:41,630
What happened?

57
00:11:43,671 --> 00:11:45,755
I have been seeing her since childhood.

58
00:11:46,046 --> 00:11:50,755
That girl's eyes, her sweet words...
they are still haunting me.

59
00:11:52,380 --> 00:11:54,380
Maybe that's all that was written in her destiny.

60
00:11:55,463 --> 00:11:57,130
We should accept it as fate and forget it.

61
00:11:57,838 --> 00:11:58,796
It's not fate...

62
00:12:00,088 --> 00:12:02,546
She was a small soul who didn't know the world.

63
00:12:02,796 --> 00:12:04,463
She fell victim to human deception.

64
00:12:07,546 --> 00:12:09,255
There are many such cheaters.

65
00:12:10,171 --> 00:12:11,463
We shouldn't just let them go.

66
00:12:12,255 --> 00:12:17,005
Fear will arise in such people only
when the public revolts and beats them with stones.

67
00:12:17,213 --> 00:12:18,838
Okay, what do you want to do now?

68
00:12:19,713 --> 00:12:20,546
We will do one thing.

69
00:12:22,546 --> 00:12:23,546
Let's expose them.

70
00:12:37,255 --> 00:12:38,713
How many did you bring?

71
00:12:39,796 --> 00:12:40,921
Three people, Swamiji.

72
00:12:43,171 --> 00:12:45,838
Your performance is declining week by week.

73
00:12:47,005 --> 00:12:48,713
Uh... well...

74
00:12:49,171 --> 00:12:50,171
Who are they?

75
00:12:51,338 --> 00:12:54,588
Two young girls and a 45-year-old lady.

76
00:12:57,213 --> 00:12:58,463
How much can we make?

77
00:12:59,546 --> 00:13:05,171
Not much from the girls, but the old lady
has a lot of money, Swamiji.

78
00:13:06,213 --> 00:13:07,088
And she's scared.

79
00:13:10,088 --> 00:13:13,921
The more scared they are,
the stronger we become.

80
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:17,963
I'm feeling tense, man.

81
00:13:18,963 --> 00:13:20,380
Maybe we should also go with them.

82
00:13:20,630 --> 00:13:23,338
Who died recently in their village?

83
00:13:24,171 --> 00:13:28,255
A girl named Mahalakshmi
failed 10th grade and jumped into a well and died.

84
00:13:29,213 --> 00:13:33,130
In the neighboring village,
four female laborers died in an auto accident.

85
00:13:35,588 --> 00:13:37,005
Hey! What are you doing here?

86
00:13:38,546 --> 00:13:39,963
The bathroom is not here, it's that way.

87
00:13:41,255 --> 00:13:41,713
Let's go.

88
00:13:46,838 --> 00:13:51,088
Swamiji is coming. Swamiji! Swamiji!
Swamiji! Swamiji, Swamiji, Swamiji.

89
00:13:51,755 --> 00:13:52,880
What is the problem?

90
00:13:53,130 --> 00:13:54,588
His name is Bhupathi Naidu.

91
00:13:54,921 --> 00:13:57,588
This is his wife, Sarojamma.

92
00:13:57,755 --> 00:14:00,713
She has been acting crazy like this for a month.

93
00:14:01,255 --> 00:14:04,505
You are an all-knowing wise man,
you must find out what's wrong, Swamiji.

94
00:14:07,255 --> 00:14:08,421
Mahalakshmi!

95
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:10,588
Mahalakshmi?

96
00:14:11,171 --> 00:14:12,171
Who is that, Swami?

97
00:14:12,796 --> 00:14:18,463
A few days ago, a girl named Mahalakshmi from their village
failed her 10th grade, jumped into a well, and died.

98
00:14:19,338 --> 00:14:24,171
Her spirit, unable to leave this world,
has possessed this woman.

99
00:14:24,255 --> 00:14:25,088
Did you see?

100
00:14:25,588 --> 00:14:31,755
The fact that Swamiji knew about Mahalakshmi's death
in their village means he is no ordinary man, Swami.

101
00:14:31,755 --> 00:14:34,005
Did you see the Swamiji's powers?

102
00:14:34,130 --> 00:14:37,671
If you had come a little earlier,
you would have found a solution sooner.

103
00:14:42,171 --> 00:14:45,213
Time itself decides when
something should happen.

104
00:14:47,213 --> 00:14:51,296
To get rid of that Mahalakshmi's affliction,
some pujas must be performed.

105
00:14:52,505 --> 00:14:54,588
My disciples will tell you about the arrangements.

106
00:14:54,838 --> 00:14:55,671
As you wish, Swami.

107
00:14:56,171 --> 00:14:57,130
Let's go, Naidu garu.

108
00:14:57,338 --> 00:14:59,130
Your wife will surely get well.

109
00:15:01,338 --> 00:15:02,338
Look, they are coming!

110
00:15:02,671 --> 00:15:06,671
I think they're caught. Quick, quick. Hop on.

111
00:15:12,005 --> 00:15:16,005
Kalabhairavananda Swamy who deceived
people with magic and spells…

112
00:15:16,005 --> 00:15:20,005
and whose lies led to a child’s unjust death…

113
00:15:20,255 --> 00:15:22,130
was finally exposed by four friends.

114
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:24,588
Will you go or not

115
00:15:24,921 --> 00:15:26,005
Hey Saithan

116
00:15:26,546 --> 00:15:27,630
Leave her and go

117
00:15:32,671 --> 00:15:33,630
Go

118
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:34,255
Go

119
00:15:34,463 --> 00:15:35,421
Go away from here

120
00:15:36,713 --> 00:15:37,671
Leave Her

121
00:15:38,005 --> 00:15:38,963
Go away from here

122
00:15:52,755 --> 00:15:57,463
In a dargah in Hyderabad's whole city,
dangerous chemicals were mixed into the incense...

123
00:15:57,463 --> 00:16:00,421
These days, girls aren't even getting
married if they step out into the streets.

124
00:16:00,963 --> 00:16:04,338
and you've gone straight onto TV to reveal
the incident. Who will marry you now?

125
00:16:06,255 --> 00:16:06,838
Mom!

126
00:16:07,796 --> 00:16:09,463
Aruna is not merely our maid.

127
00:16:09,796 --> 00:16:10,796
She’s family to us.

128
00:16:11,005 --> 00:16:12,838
She’s been by our side for years.

129
00:16:12,921 --> 00:16:15,671
Her daughter is died.

130
00:16:16,171 --> 00:16:18,255
Mom, she has a sleepwalking issue.

131
00:16:19,421 --> 00:16:22,130
If only we had waited for a few days,
it would’ve been gone.

132
00:16:23,005 --> 00:16:26,546
Unfortunately, the Swamiji was cruel
and killed her in the meantime.

133
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:29,130
Nevertheless, I told her repeatedly.

134
00:16:29,296 --> 00:16:31,463
To bring her to a hospital for a check-up.

135
00:16:31,588 --> 00:16:34,921
She spoke of spirits and
took her to someone unknown.

136
00:16:36,130 --> 00:16:37,838
There will be plenty of people who betray others.

137
00:16:38,046 --> 00:16:39,671
We should watch our step.

138
00:16:42,171 --> 00:16:43,838
Hey, do you know the crazy news?

139
00:16:44,546 --> 00:16:45,463
Congrats, buddy!

140
00:16:45,755 --> 00:16:46,588
I'm so happy!

141
00:16:47,838 --> 00:16:49,380
Hey, Naina! Come, come, come.

142
00:16:50,171 --> 00:16:51,713
Another member is about to be added to our group.

143
00:16:52,171 --> 00:16:52,921
Who?

144
00:16:53,296 --> 00:16:55,171
Little Aparna and Vinay is on the way.

145
00:16:55,505 --> 00:16:56,171
Really?

146
00:16:56,213 --> 00:16:57,255
Yeah!
- For real?

147
00:16:57,755 --> 00:16:59,713
I came to know when i got doubt in morning

148
00:16:59,796 --> 00:17:00,630
Congrats Dear

149
00:17:02,838 --> 00:17:04,171
So happy for you!

150
00:17:04,671 --> 00:17:04,838
Thank you!

151
00:17:14,255 --> 00:17:20,130
Aparna... why are there tears in your eyes
at such a happy time?

152
00:17:21,255 --> 00:17:26,005
You know, it's been five years since
Vinay's parents last spoke to him.

153
00:17:35,713 --> 00:17:42,171
I've been through hell these five years with the guilty feeling
that he became distant from his parents because he married me.

154
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:46,963
Many times I felt that if I left him and went far away...

155
00:17:47,838 --> 00:17:50,171
He would get close to his parents again.

156
00:17:51,546 --> 00:17:53,130
But I didn't have the courage.

157
00:17:54,046 --> 00:17:55,005
How could I leave?

158
00:17:56,255 --> 00:17:57,588
He is my life.

159
00:17:59,005 --> 00:18:01,880
But whenever I was sad,
he would lovingly console me, saying...

160
00:18:02,421 --> 00:18:05,630
They will be angry with us only
as long as it's just the two of us.

161
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:10,296
But if we have a child, they will come and...

162
00:18:10,713 --> 00:18:12,255
Reconcile with us even if we say no.

163
00:18:13,963 --> 00:18:15,421
After all this time, that wish is coming true.

164
00:18:17,630 --> 00:18:20,088
Marriage, kids... everything is fulfilled in our life.

165
00:18:20,546 --> 00:18:21,505
What about you?

166
00:18:23,755 --> 00:18:26,588
Will you ever tell Nayana that
you love her in this lifetime or not?

167
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:29,421
Hey, speak softly. She'll hear.

168
00:18:29,463 --> 00:18:32,880
Let her hear. You won't express it anyway,
at least she'll know this way.

169
00:18:34,713 --> 00:18:36,630
Hey, we've been friends since childhood.

170
00:18:37,130 --> 00:18:40,213
Have you ever spent a single
moment without thinking about her?

171
00:18:40,421 --> 00:18:43,338
For her sake, you even gave up
your dream of going abroad.

172
00:18:43,421 --> 00:18:46,380
You took a small job that doesn't suit
you at all and stayed with us.

173
00:18:47,755 --> 00:18:51,171
After doing all this, if you don't
at least tell her this...

174
00:18:53,005 --> 00:18:55,463
Once it slips through your hands,
you can't get it back.

175
00:19:13,671 --> 00:19:19,380
"That moon in the sky,
won't it land in your hands"

176
00:19:19,671 --> 00:19:24,338
"If the word friendship exists in life?"

177
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:31,755
"Any distance becomes closer,
any hardship becomes pleasant"

178
00:19:31,921 --> 00:19:36,880
"If the mantra of 'friendship' is in your heart"

179
00:19:38,213 --> 00:19:41,296
"In a heart burning like a furnace"

180
00:19:41,338 --> 00:19:44,171
"It comes like a cool moonlight"

181
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:49,671
"In a series of bitter experiences,
it shares sweetness"

182
00:19:50,505 --> 00:19:53,630
"Friendship, it weaves so many little smiles"

183
00:19:53,630 --> 00:19:56,588
"Friendship, it showers so many new colors"

184
00:19:56,671 --> 00:20:02,880
"Friendship, like a dream taking form,
it stood right in front of you"

185
00:20:02,921 --> 00:20:05,921
"Friendship, it sings lullabies like a mother"

186
00:20:05,921 --> 00:20:08,921
"Friendship, it shows the way like a father"

187
00:20:08,921 --> 00:20:15,005
"Friendship, it promised to be with you,
anytime, anywhere"

188
00:20:27,505 --> 00:20:29,838
"So many unforgettable memories"

189
00:20:30,588 --> 00:20:33,255
"So many unstoppable journeys"

190
00:20:33,671 --> 00:20:36,880
"So many mischievous talks"

191
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:39,963
"are all outlines of friendship."

192
00:20:40,046 --> 00:20:42,130
"So many beautiful poems"

193
00:20:42,796 --> 00:20:45,671
"So many destinies of our own"

194
00:20:46,005 --> 00:20:49,130
"So many indelible histories"

195
00:20:49,130 --> 00:20:51,671
"Friends are our true assets"

196
00:20:52,171 --> 00:20:54,880
"A hug amidst tears is friendship"

197
00:20:55,338 --> 00:20:57,963
"The greatest of all is friendship"

198
00:20:58,338 --> 00:21:04,380
"More than love in life, like a mother's love, it's a truth
that it reaches you through a path that cannot be found"

199
00:21:04,505 --> 00:21:07,505
"Friendship, it weaves so many little smiles"

200
00:21:07,505 --> 00:21:10,630
"Friendship, it showers so many new colors"

201
00:21:10,630 --> 00:21:16,838
"Like a dream taking form,
it stood right in front of you"

202
00:21:16,838 --> 00:21:19,921
"Friendship, it sings lullabies like a mother"

203
00:21:19,921 --> 00:21:22,963
"Friendship, it shows the way like a father"

204
00:21:22,963 --> 00:21:29,046
"Friendship, it promised to be with you,
anytime, anywhere"

205
00:21:35,296 --> 00:21:36,088
Who is he?

206
00:21:37,046 --> 00:21:38,338
He is our next target.

207
00:21:38,505 --> 00:21:39,505
His name is Adhidev.

208
00:21:39,630 --> 00:21:42,630
He's not like the godmen and
swamis we've dealt with so far.

209
00:21:43,213 --> 00:21:43,546
Meaning?

210
00:21:44,005 --> 00:21:45,880
He's a top neurosurgeon from America.

211
00:21:46,213 --> 00:21:47,171
A neurosurgeon?

212
00:21:47,338 --> 00:21:47,713
Yes.

213
00:21:48,546 --> 00:21:49,921
He's an expert brain surgeon.

214
00:21:50,463 --> 00:21:52,338
Father Indian, mother Pakistani.

215
00:21:53,005 --> 00:21:53,796
They are also doctors.

216
00:21:54,213 --> 00:21:55,796
A family that settled in the US long ago.

217
00:21:59,421 --> 00:22:00,671
I can't believe it.

218
00:22:01,921 --> 00:22:06,713
A person who did research on human
brains doing such things... it's unbelievable.

219
00:22:07,171 --> 00:22:10,546
10 years back, his wife died
due to a psychological problem.

220
00:22:12,338 --> 00:22:14,880
A case was filed against him, blaming him for it.

221
00:22:15,255 --> 00:22:18,171
But the case was dismissed due to lack of evidence.

222
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:22,796
After that, he left America.

223
00:22:23,380 --> 00:22:25,380
Nobody knows where he went or what happened to him.

224
00:22:26,046 --> 00:22:28,213
He just vanished without a trace.

225
00:22:28,671 --> 00:22:35,630
But the strange thing is, after all these years, he was seen
in a remote village on the Andhra-Orissa border, exorcising spirits.

226
00:22:36,296 --> 00:22:36,796
What?

227
00:22:37,005 --> 00:22:38,588
There is a leaked video about his wife.

228
00:22:38,838 --> 00:22:43,046
This video was recorded on a CCTV footage
in her final moments before she died.

229
00:22:43,255 --> 00:22:45,296
It's a bit disturbing. Let's watch it.

230
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:26,463
So, his wife became like that because of him?

231
00:23:27,921 --> 00:23:29,838
No, I'm feeling scared for some reason.

232
00:23:30,755 --> 00:23:31,713
Let's not get involved with him.

233
00:23:32,213 --> 00:23:35,213
What we've done so far is enough.
Let's stop all this.

234
00:23:35,588 --> 00:23:36,338
Stop it?

235
00:23:37,255 --> 00:23:39,546
What we did until now is different.
This is completely different.

236
00:23:39,963 --> 00:23:43,630
Because of sociopaths like him,
our society is becoming more poisonous.

237
00:23:43,921 --> 00:23:46,338
No, there's no question of leaving him.

238
00:23:49,963 --> 00:23:50,838
My opinion is the same.

239
00:23:51,505 --> 00:23:52,130
Let's expose him.

240
00:23:57,213 --> 00:23:57,630
No.

241
00:23:59,546 --> 00:24:00,088
No.

242
00:24:00,296 --> 00:24:00,796
Hey!

243
00:24:02,380 --> 00:24:03,630
Hey, Aparna!
- Aparna!

244
00:24:09,671 --> 00:24:12,838
Even your mother is saying no.
Why are you so stubborn?

245
00:24:12,921 --> 00:24:13,713
Shut up and come.

246
00:24:14,588 --> 00:24:15,130
Shall we go?

247
00:24:15,296 --> 00:24:17,130
I'm getting negative vibes
for some reason.

248
00:24:17,463 --> 00:24:18,921
Think once, guys.

249
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:20,838
Why all this?

250
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,171
What if the same happened to our baby?

251
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:25,838
Why did you hit him like that?

252
00:24:26,088 --> 00:24:28,588
Then what? Why did he speak like that,
without sense?

253
00:24:31,921 --> 00:24:32,505
Let's go.

254
00:24:55,171 --> 00:25:02,171
"Little Krishna, little Krishna,
with chubby cheeks, my baby Krishna"

255
00:25:09,171 --> 00:25:10,546
Baby Krishna...

256
00:25:12,296 --> 00:25:15,213
Hey! How much longer will it take?

257
00:25:15,255 --> 00:25:16,880
I'm coming!

258
00:25:16,921 --> 00:25:19,463
You've been saying the same for half an hour.

259
00:25:21,796 --> 00:25:22,588
Shall we go, dear?

260
00:25:22,755 --> 00:25:23,838
Come on, come on, come on.

261
00:25:26,546 --> 00:25:27,046
Here.

262
00:25:31,171 --> 00:25:31,671
Shall I get on?

263
00:25:31,671 --> 00:25:32,421
Get on.

264
00:25:34,838 --> 00:25:35,838
Uncle, wait a minute!

265
00:25:36,296 --> 00:25:37,463
What happened again?

266
00:25:37,463 --> 00:25:38,963
Hold on, I'll be right back.

267
00:25:45,296 --> 00:25:45,838
Found it!

268
00:25:51,671 --> 00:25:52,463
Look at this.

269
00:25:52,755 --> 00:25:56,505
It doesn't look like we're going to a wedding,
it looks like we're going for his wedding proposals.

270
00:25:57,463 --> 00:25:58,671
That's how heroic my son looks.

271
00:25:58,671 --> 00:25:59,713
Alright, get on.

272
00:25:59,838 --> 00:26:01,755
My mom used to say the same thing when I was little.

273
00:26:02,130 --> 00:26:03,505
But now look, in your hands.

274
00:26:04,671 --> 00:26:07,380
Auntie! We are going to the wedding,
take care of the house!

275
00:26:07,380 --> 00:26:08,671
We will be back by night!

276
00:26:29,630 --> 00:26:30,796
Oh Lord!

277
00:26:31,505 --> 00:26:32,630
Oh Lord!

278
00:26:34,130 --> 00:26:35,130
My daughter...

279
00:26:37,005 --> 00:26:38,921
You have to save her.

280
00:26:40,255 --> 00:26:40,963
We named her...

281
00:26:41,838 --> 00:26:45,588
Shivamma,
after you, my lord.

282
00:26:47,588 --> 00:26:49,421
Don't know what evil wind touched her...

283
00:26:50,171 --> 00:26:52,380
The child is writhing in pain.

284
00:26:54,171 --> 00:26:54,713
Dear!

285
00:26:57,213 --> 00:27:00,755
Lord... you have to save her.

286
00:27:02,671 --> 00:27:07,130
There's some Swami in the next village.

287
00:27:07,755 --> 00:27:11,755
They say he exorcises demons and cures everyone...

288
00:27:12,421 --> 00:27:14,880
So I was taking her there.

289
00:27:15,463 --> 00:27:16,713
Lord...

290
00:27:17,255 --> 00:27:20,338
With your grace...

291
00:27:21,255 --> 00:27:25,296
Always watch over her, Swami.

292
00:27:26,630 --> 00:27:28,213
Always watch over her.

293
00:27:30,588 --> 00:27:31,755
Watch over her.

294
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:34,838
Bless her.

295
00:27:35,796 --> 00:27:36,463
Lord!

296
00:27:40,463 --> 00:27:41,171
Come, dear.

297
00:27:46,338 --> 00:27:47,130
Come!

298
00:27:47,921 --> 00:27:48,630
Come!

299
00:27:52,130 --> 00:27:53,338
Lord Shiva!

300
00:28:16,005 --> 00:28:18,921
Son, sit carefully. Hold on tight, dear.

301
00:28:19,255 --> 00:28:20,338
Look, look!

302
00:28:20,546 --> 00:28:22,838
Did you see? The squirrels are so cute, right?

303
00:28:27,255 --> 00:28:27,963
Sorry.

304
00:28:31,630 --> 00:28:33,421
Look, a turning is coming!

305
00:28:36,963 --> 00:28:38,338
I'm saying sorry, right?

306
00:28:44,171 --> 00:28:47,046
Sankranti festival is coming,
let's buy clothes for our son.

307
00:28:47,130 --> 00:28:48,546
Let's go to the shop as soon as it's morning.

308
00:28:48,588 --> 00:28:49,463
Sure, dear.

309
00:28:49,588 --> 00:28:51,630
Hey, she's saying sorry, you know.

310
00:28:53,963 --> 00:28:55,213
Why are you being so stubborn?

311
00:29:01,838 --> 00:29:02,213
Hey!

312
00:29:02,963 --> 00:29:04,463
Look at the monkeys, look!

313
00:29:04,630 --> 00:29:05,963
They look just like your mom!

314
00:29:05,963 --> 00:29:07,130
You...

315
00:29:09,713 --> 00:29:10,755
At least you tell him.

316
00:29:12,338 --> 00:29:13,588
Why are you angry at monkeys?

317
00:29:13,588 --> 00:29:14,505
They're our relatives, right?

318
00:29:15,463 --> 00:29:16,171
Dear!

319
00:29:31,421 --> 00:29:32,630
He's going to fall.

320
00:29:32,713 --> 00:29:33,713
Hold him tight!

321
00:29:34,046 --> 00:29:34,546
Dear!

322
00:29:40,713 --> 00:29:41,713
Son...

323
00:29:45,463 --> 00:29:46,255
Lord Shiva!

324
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:50,880
He's fine, dear.

325
00:29:51,588 --> 00:29:52,505
Let's go.

326
00:29:54,505 --> 00:29:55,380
Punyavathi!

327
00:29:59,755 --> 00:30:00,713
Punyavathi!

328
00:30:13,338 --> 00:30:14,005
Punyavathi!

329
00:30:19,588 --> 00:30:20,338
Punyavathi!

330
00:30:22,380 --> 00:30:23,255
Punyavathi!

331
00:30:24,046 --> 00:30:24,880
Punyavathi!

332
00:30:27,505 --> 00:30:28,463
Punyavathi!

333
00:30:31,130 --> 00:30:32,130
What happened?

334
00:30:33,046 --> 00:30:33,671
Stop!

335
00:30:34,213 --> 00:30:34,796
Stop!

336
00:30:38,755 --> 00:30:39,130
Brother!

337
00:30:40,171 --> 00:30:41,171
Take care of the child.

338
00:30:42,921 --> 00:30:43,546
Brother...

339
00:30:43,796 --> 00:30:44,880
What happened?
- My wife.

340
00:30:44,921 --> 00:30:47,755
She fell... Save her, brother...

341
00:30:48,213 --> 00:30:48,838
Brother!

342
00:30:48,838 --> 00:30:50,255
Help me, brother...

343
00:30:51,213 --> 00:30:52,338
You stay here.

344
00:30:55,130 --> 00:30:55,671
Punyavathi!

345
00:30:58,630 --> 00:30:59,838
Punyavathi!

346
00:31:00,796 --> 00:31:01,921
Punyavathi!

347
00:31:02,880 --> 00:31:03,630
Oh god...

348
00:31:04,588 --> 00:31:05,880
What happened, God?

349
00:31:12,130 --> 00:31:13,421
Blood...

350
00:31:17,046 --> 00:31:18,588
Oh God...

351
00:31:55,588 --> 00:31:56,880
Lord Shiva!

352
00:32:02,213 --> 00:32:03,838
Lord Shiva!

353
00:32:24,130 --> 00:32:24,963
Slowly...

354
00:32:25,630 --> 00:32:28,088
Please make way, sir.

355
00:32:30,796 --> 00:32:31,671
Slowly, child.

356
00:32:33,421 --> 00:32:34,005
Come.

357
00:33:13,130 --> 00:33:13,880
Swami...

358
00:33:27,213 --> 00:33:28,421
Is it Adhidev?

359
00:33:28,838 --> 00:33:29,755
Yes.

360
00:33:52,796 --> 00:33:54,088
Don't you worry.

361
00:33:54,505 --> 00:33:56,963
This is a disorder in the brain
caused by anemia.

362
00:33:57,713 --> 00:34:00,463
Show her to a good doctor, it will be cured.
- Okay, Swami.

363
00:34:02,171 --> 00:34:02,921
Come, dear.

364
00:34:36,755 --> 00:34:38,588
A spirit has possessed her.

365
00:34:39,255 --> 00:34:40,255
A ritual needs to be performed.

366
00:34:40,421 --> 00:34:40,880
Swami...

367
00:34:41,546 --> 00:34:42,880
Take her to the ashram.

368
00:34:43,338 --> 00:34:46,921
It's because of people like him that human sacrifices
and black magic rituals are happening.

369
00:34:47,130 --> 00:34:51,171
In the name of salvation,
they are driving people to suicide.

370
00:34:53,755 --> 00:34:54,421
Swami...

371
00:34:55,671 --> 00:34:56,755
My daughter...

372
00:34:58,046 --> 00:34:58,671
Swami...

373
00:35:01,380 --> 00:35:02,213
Swami...

374
00:35:18,463 --> 00:35:20,796
No spirit has possessed your daughter.

375
00:35:21,588 --> 00:35:23,505
It is just a health problem.

376
00:35:24,171 --> 00:35:26,005
Show her to a good doctor.

377
00:35:26,005 --> 00:35:28,505
So my daughter will get well, sir?

378
00:35:28,505 --> 00:35:29,963
She will definitely be cured.

379
00:35:31,380 --> 00:35:32,130
Swami...

380
00:35:32,171 --> 00:35:33,088
May you live a long and happy life.

381
00:35:34,463 --> 00:35:35,255
You can leave.

382
00:35:35,255 --> 00:35:36,005
Okay, Swami.

383
00:35:38,338 --> 00:35:42,130
Lord Shiva has listened to our pleas.
Nothing will happen to our child.

384
00:35:42,130 --> 00:35:42,755
Yes, dear.

385
00:36:07,005 --> 00:36:07,963
Dear!

386
00:36:16,755 --> 00:36:17,130
Hey!

387
00:36:52,588 --> 00:36:53,338
Stop.

388
00:36:57,171 --> 00:36:57,880
Who are you?

389
00:36:59,338 --> 00:37:00,505
Why did you come here?

390
00:37:01,421 --> 00:37:02,421
What do you want?

391
00:37:02,505 --> 00:37:04,130
We're the ones
who should be asking that question.

392
00:37:06,921 --> 00:37:08,171
What is it that you want?

393
00:37:09,421 --> 00:37:10,380
We've read about you.

394
00:37:11,463 --> 00:37:12,713
Doctor Adidev.

395
00:37:13,255 --> 00:37:14,463
Top neurosurgeon.

396
00:37:15,921 --> 00:37:20,588
Why have you left all that and
are playing with these poor people's lives?

397
00:37:22,463 --> 00:37:25,463
Sometimes, a purpose is born out of tragedy.

398
00:37:26,255 --> 00:37:28,838
That purpose defines our life's destination...

399
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:34,588
Is destroying innocent lives in the
name of spirits and ghosts your destination?

400
00:37:35,755 --> 00:37:38,296
Not to destroy, but to save.

401
00:37:39,005 --> 00:37:43,005
In the external world you know,
humans have only two problems.

402
00:37:43,421 --> 00:37:46,796
One is physical problems,
the second is mental problems.

403
00:37:47,130 --> 00:37:49,838
There are many people out there to solve them.

404
00:37:50,755 --> 00:37:56,755
But there is another dark world, unknown to you,
which you're even afraid to imagine.

405
00:37:57,838 --> 00:38:00,338
People who can solve the problems in it...

406
00:38:01,088 --> 00:38:02,755
Are very few.

407
00:38:03,046 --> 00:38:05,421
That's why I took that responsibility.

408
00:38:05,755 --> 00:38:06,921
After being so educated,

409
00:38:06,921 --> 00:38:10,130
aren't you ashamed to spread
these superstitions among people?

410
00:38:10,630 --> 00:38:14,838
Until it becomes our experience,
anything is a superstition.

411
00:38:15,213 --> 00:38:18,546
The moment it becomes our experience,
it becomes a belief.

412
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:20,046
Once upon a time, I too...

413
00:38:20,921 --> 00:38:24,671
More strongly than you, opposed all of this.

414
00:38:24,963 --> 00:38:26,463
But my wife's death...

415
00:38:26,963 --> 00:38:28,963
Introduced me to spirits.

416
00:38:30,463 --> 00:38:32,005
Your own body...

417
00:38:32,671 --> 00:38:37,713
Do you know how terrifying the conflict is
when a spirit that is not yours occupies it?

418
00:38:40,796 --> 00:38:45,588
Like every nerve in you is being snapped,
like your body is burning in a furnace of fire...

419
00:38:45,796 --> 00:38:50,671
Like hundreds of venomous snakes
are biting your body all at once...

420
00:38:50,880 --> 00:38:54,505
While an unbearable gale swirls in your brain...

421
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:59,963
Unable to distinguish between night and day,
unable to know the difference between water and fire...

422
00:39:00,671 --> 00:39:03,463
Unable to differentiate between a human and an animal...

423
00:39:03,671 --> 00:39:06,380
With the boundaries of earth and sky blurring...

424
00:39:06,505 --> 00:39:11,630
Left in a state of madness where you don't understand
what the problem is, how to explain it...

425
00:39:11,671 --> 00:39:13,380
Or to whom to explain it...

426
00:39:13,505 --> 00:39:15,588
Coming to me for help...

427
00:39:15,838 --> 00:39:18,880
For these people,
this is the treatment I am providing.

428
00:39:19,046 --> 00:39:26,380
People like you are destroying society by creating mass hysteria
about ghosts and demons, turning even good people mad.

429
00:39:28,171 --> 00:39:31,213
So you're saying spirits don't exist?

430
00:39:31,796 --> 00:39:32,630
Are you mad?

431
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:33,796
We're telling you they don't exist.

432
00:39:36,463 --> 00:39:38,671
What if I prove that spirits exist?

433
00:39:46,796 --> 00:39:54,880
The human soul is immortal, infinite, omniscient,
and does not die with the death of the body...

434
00:39:56,171 --> 00:39:58,213
As Swami Vivekananda said.

435
00:40:00,130 --> 00:40:03,046
In three days, I will introduce you to spirits.

436
00:40:43,171 --> 00:40:48,546
Just like people, some places
are cursed right from their birth.

437
00:40:49,088 --> 00:40:52,838
Later, they gradually become abodes for spirits.

438
00:40:53,505 --> 00:40:54,671
This is one such place.

439
00:40:55,588 --> 00:41:03,296
During the construction of this house,
the mason killed two of his workers and then killed himself.

440
00:41:05,338 --> 00:41:08,338
After many inauspicious events,
this house was completed.

441
00:41:09,296 --> 00:41:11,463
On the day of the housewarming,
there was a big function.

442
00:41:11,880 --> 00:41:14,088
After it went off very happily...

443
00:41:14,588 --> 00:41:16,713
Nobody knows what happened that night...

444
00:41:17,296 --> 00:41:18,796
But the owner of this house...

445
00:41:19,130 --> 00:41:23,005
Killed his entire family and then killed himself.

446
00:41:26,838 --> 00:41:31,046
Even though people died,
hopes for this place didn't.

447
00:41:31,130 --> 00:41:33,671
One person bought this house,
planning to turn it into a resort.

448
00:41:33,755 --> 00:41:36,713
To dispel the fear among people about this place...

449
00:41:37,338 --> 00:41:38,755
He himself first...

450
00:41:39,005 --> 00:41:42,921
Came with his family to spend
ten days in this house.

451
00:41:44,296 --> 00:41:45,796
Nobody knows what happened...

452
00:41:46,630 --> 00:41:47,921
But two days later...

453
00:41:48,713 --> 00:41:50,505
He killed his wife and children...

454
00:41:51,088 --> 00:41:53,005
And then jumped from the top and died.

455
00:41:54,880 --> 00:42:00,046
In those incidents, no one
who could tell what happened in this house survived.

456
00:42:02,713 --> 00:42:06,338
But seeing all this, I understood one thing.

457
00:42:06,755 --> 00:42:14,588
For many years, some evil spirits that have held
this area captive consider this place their right.

458
00:42:15,463 --> 00:42:20,130
They are unable to accept the
arrival of humans into this place.

459
00:42:21,421 --> 00:42:27,130
After all these years, you, who believe all this is trash,
have come before me.

460
00:42:28,921 --> 00:42:32,421
If you can spend three days in this house...

461
00:42:33,921 --> 00:42:36,380
And prove that there are no spirits here...

462
00:42:36,380 --> 00:42:39,505
I will admit that the theory I've
believed in for so long is wrong...

463
00:42:39,505 --> 00:42:42,755
And I will be ready to do whatever you say.

464
00:42:44,755 --> 00:42:46,088
Are you ready?

465
00:42:51,046 --> 00:42:51,755
We're ready.

466
00:42:59,088 --> 00:42:59,796
Come.

467
00:43:03,838 --> 00:43:04,713
Be careful.

468
00:43:17,171 --> 00:43:20,171
I told you, the spirits here are very dangerous.

469
00:43:20,296 --> 00:43:24,213
These arrangements are to ensure
no harm comes to your lives because of them.

470
00:43:41,505 --> 00:43:42,588
The work is done, swami.

471
00:43:45,671 --> 00:43:48,213
I've made some arrangements for you to stay here.

472
00:43:48,546 --> 00:43:49,588
We shall meet again.

473
00:43:51,296 --> 00:43:52,088
One thing.

474
00:43:52,505 --> 00:43:58,255
Under no circumstances should you cross this
blocked-off area and go anywhere outside.

475
00:44:49,213 --> 00:44:50,755
For some reason, I'm scared.

476
00:44:51,213 --> 00:44:51,588
Why?

477
00:44:53,755 --> 00:44:58,046
Some guy attacking us at the ashram,
the things that happened in this house...

478
00:45:00,963 --> 00:45:03,963
Seeing all this, I'm getting some unknown,
uneasy feeling.

479
00:45:04,088 --> 00:45:08,171
Look, stop labeling every
unknown uneasy feeling as fear.

480
00:45:09,130 --> 00:45:12,505
Firstly, the guy who attacked us at the ashram
was some mentally disturbed person.

481
00:45:13,213 --> 00:45:16,630
And, about this house?
Those are all stories he made up.

482
00:45:17,463 --> 00:45:20,213
See, he's playing games with our minds.

483
00:45:20,713 --> 00:45:22,588
He's an expert brain surgeon.

484
00:45:23,380 --> 00:45:25,005
He's playing games with our brains.

485
00:45:25,296 --> 00:45:26,838
So, be very careful. Okay?

486
00:45:30,880 --> 00:45:32,505
Nothing will happen. Let's go.

487
00:45:36,255 --> 00:45:38,213
Hey, why are you so scared?

488
00:45:38,921 --> 00:45:39,630
I'm here, right?

489
00:47:40,213 --> 00:47:42,005
Aparna, what... What happened?

490
00:47:44,713 --> 00:47:45,505
What happened?

491
00:47:48,546 --> 00:47:49,046
Vinay!

492
00:47:49,338 --> 00:47:51,921
No matter what you say,
I'm not convinced for some reason.

493
00:47:52,255 --> 00:47:53,338
Let's not stay here.

494
00:47:53,463 --> 00:47:54,630
Let's go, Vinay.

495
00:47:54,671 --> 00:47:56,088
Why are you scared?

496
00:47:56,255 --> 00:47:59,005
My fear is not for myself,
but for our baby.

497
00:47:59,838 --> 00:48:01,171
Nothing will happen to our baby.

498
00:48:01,255 --> 00:48:02,880
You, me, our baby.

499
00:48:02,921 --> 00:48:04,088
We'll be happy wherever we are.

500
00:48:04,338 --> 00:48:06,005
First, just let go of all your fears.

501
00:48:06,671 --> 00:48:08,296
Just think of it as we've come for a three-day outing.

502
00:48:10,255 --> 00:48:10,921
Nothing will happen.

503
00:48:11,588 --> 00:48:12,088
Let's go.

504
00:48:14,963 --> 00:48:15,963
What happened again?

505
00:48:20,963 --> 00:48:22,213
I smell something.

506
00:48:22,838 --> 00:48:25,088
I smell something like burning skin, Vinay.

507
00:48:26,296 --> 00:48:28,296
Aparna, this place hasn't been used for a long time.

508
00:48:28,338 --> 00:48:31,421
Maybe that's why you're getting this feeling.

509
00:48:31,588 --> 00:48:33,088
There's nothing here. Let's go.
- No, Vinay.

510
00:48:33,338 --> 00:48:34,380
Something...
- Let's go, let's go.

511
00:48:34,838 --> 00:48:36,838
Aparna, I'm telling you there's nothing.

512
00:48:36,838 --> 00:48:38,380
There is some smell.
- Come.

513
00:48:47,755 --> 00:48:49,338
Hi. What brings you here?

514
00:48:50,296 --> 00:48:53,838
The ascetic said something would happen
if we crossed that place, right?

515
00:48:53,963 --> 00:48:55,255
I came to see what would happen.

516
00:48:56,838 --> 00:48:58,255
But Aparna looks very dull.

517
00:48:58,338 --> 00:49:00,213
She is very scared.

518
00:49:00,713 --> 00:49:01,588
Let her be scared.

519
00:49:01,921 --> 00:49:04,630
Let all the fear inside her come out.

520
00:49:05,046 --> 00:49:10,046
After three days, when she realizes there's nothing here,
courage will take the place of fear.

521
00:49:10,171 --> 00:49:12,255
After that, she'll never be scared in her life.

522
00:49:13,963 --> 00:49:15,796
Anyway, Vinay is with her.

523
00:49:16,380 --> 00:49:19,713
In a way, it's her good fortune
that Vinay is with her.

524
00:49:20,463 --> 00:49:22,713
Your future wife is also a lucky one.

525
00:49:23,463 --> 00:49:26,755
As far as I know,
you too will take good care of your wife.

526
00:49:27,380 --> 00:49:30,463
If you want, I'll give that girl
that guarantee during the matchmaking.

527
00:49:31,671 --> 00:49:33,880
Is she saying it knowingly or unknowingly?

528
00:49:34,338 --> 00:49:34,755
Hey!

529
00:50:02,671 --> 00:50:04,505
What the ascetic said is true.

530
00:50:05,546 --> 00:50:08,630
We crossed those markings and came out.

531
00:50:09,588 --> 00:50:11,130
This happened.

532
00:51:11,921 --> 00:51:12,921
Who are you?

533
00:51:15,213 --> 00:51:16,088
Who are you?

534
00:51:26,005 --> 00:51:26,963
I'm asking you.

535
00:51:27,213 --> 00:51:28,130
Who are you?

536
00:51:42,838 --> 00:51:43,713
Who are you?

537
00:51:44,338 --> 00:51:46,671
Why did you try to attack them?

538
00:51:46,713 --> 00:51:49,213
What is your connection to them?

539
00:51:49,671 --> 00:51:51,421
Hey, I'm asking you.

540
00:51:51,588 --> 00:51:52,505
Who are you?

541
00:51:52,671 --> 00:51:53,796
Will you tell me or not?

542
00:51:55,005 --> 00:51:55,546
Tell me!

543
00:51:57,171 --> 00:52:01,255
I really don't know what that name is.

544
00:52:01,546 --> 00:52:06,546
I'm not asking about this body you've possessed,
I'm asking about you.

545
00:52:08,463 --> 00:52:11,880
My forehead is burning.
Let go!

546
00:52:12,671 --> 00:52:13,796
Tell me.

547
00:52:14,005 --> 00:52:15,296
Tell me your name.

548
00:52:15,380 --> 00:52:16,296
Tell me.

549
00:52:19,630 --> 00:52:21,713
Punyavathi.

550
00:52:26,005 --> 00:52:28,046
What is your connection to them?

551
00:52:29,588 --> 00:52:33,255
They are the ones who killed me.

552
00:52:36,421 --> 00:52:43,463
Unjustly, they separated me
from my husband and my son.

553
00:52:45,171 --> 00:52:46,130
How did it happen?

554
00:52:46,338 --> 00:52:52,880
When I was going to a wedding
with my husband and son...

555
00:52:53,088 --> 00:52:59,505
These three scoundrels hit our vehicle
while driving and caused an accident.

556
00:53:00,838 --> 00:53:05,463
At that same time, he...
He came near me.

557
00:53:05,505 --> 00:53:09,005
That's why I possessed him.

558
00:53:10,421 --> 00:53:11,505
I won't spare them.

559
00:53:12,296 --> 00:53:14,505
I won't spare anyone.

560
00:53:16,338 --> 00:53:18,963
I will kill everyone.

561
00:53:19,421 --> 00:53:26,255
In the end, if you get in my way,
I will kill you too.

562
00:57:19,130 --> 00:57:20,005
Who is it?

563
00:57:28,088 --> 00:57:28,963
Who are you?

564
00:57:37,088 --> 00:57:38,088
Who are you?

565
00:58:12,921 --> 00:58:13,921
Who are you?

566
00:58:18,088 --> 00:58:18,588
Aparna!

567
00:58:19,796 --> 00:58:20,546
Aparna, what happened?

568
00:58:20,588 --> 00:58:21,088
Aparna!

569
00:58:21,171 --> 00:58:22,338
What happened?
Why did she scream?

570
00:58:23,213 --> 00:58:24,338
What happened, Aparna?

571
00:58:24,713 --> 00:58:25,505
There...

572
00:58:27,755 --> 00:58:28,838
There's something there.

573
00:58:29,213 --> 00:58:30,838
Aparna, there's nothing there.

574
00:58:31,505 --> 00:58:32,671
You must've had a nightmare.

575
00:58:32,963 --> 00:58:33,755
No.

576
00:58:34,713 --> 00:58:35,796
There's something there.

577
00:58:35,796 --> 00:58:37,046
Aparna, there's nothing there.

578
00:58:37,088 --> 00:58:38,755
No, it's just like me.

579
00:58:39,088 --> 00:58:40,505
Aparna, there's nothing there.

580
00:58:40,588 --> 00:58:40,921
No!

581
00:58:40,921 --> 00:58:41,546
Who, Aparna?

582
00:58:41,546 --> 00:58:43,588
It's like I've been burnt.

583
00:58:46,546 --> 00:58:49,630
Something is there.
Let's get out of here.

584
00:58:49,630 --> 00:58:51,088
Okay, okay, okay.
- Please.

585
00:58:51,338 --> 00:58:52,421
Okay.

586
00:58:53,046 --> 00:58:55,421
Will you run away scared
just because of a bad dream?

587
00:58:56,088 --> 00:58:57,338
You sleep peacefully.

588
00:58:57,505 --> 00:58:59,380
Vinay, take care of her.
- Okay.

589
00:59:01,296 --> 00:59:02,296
Okay?

590
00:59:02,588 --> 00:59:03,005
Take care.

591
00:59:03,005 --> 00:59:04,671
Let's go, please.

592
00:59:04,755 --> 00:59:05,255
Aparna!

593
00:59:05,796 --> 00:59:06,213
Nayana.

594
00:59:09,255 --> 00:59:11,755
If you promise not to get angry,
I'll tell you something.

595
00:59:12,380 --> 00:59:13,088
What is it?

596
00:59:15,130 --> 00:59:19,880
I'm also feeling... I don't know...
a strange, uneasy feeling.

597
00:59:20,755 --> 00:59:21,713
You too?

598
00:59:22,421 --> 00:59:28,088
It's true, Nayana. A sort of...
an unknown smell, a scent is coming.

599
00:59:29,838 --> 00:59:31,671
You're also talking just like Aparna.

600
00:59:32,630 --> 00:59:34,963
It's nothing. It's already late.
Go and sleep.

601
01:01:13,838 --> 01:01:14,838
What is this?

602
01:01:43,755 --> 01:01:44,338
Kalyan!

603
01:01:45,296 --> 01:01:46,130
Kalyan!

604
01:01:48,421 --> 01:01:51,463
Nayana! - You were right.
I'm getting that smell too.

605
01:01:52,671 --> 01:01:53,505
Is it?

606
01:01:53,505 --> 01:01:56,713
That smell... is creating a hallucination.

607
01:01:56,838 --> 01:01:58,755
Just like Aparna, I got that feeling too.

608
01:02:00,255 --> 01:02:05,213
That Adidev is definitely injecting some drugs...

609
01:02:05,421 --> 01:02:10,005
Into the air and doing something to us, Kalyan.

610
01:02:10,005 --> 01:02:10,713
Drugs?

611
01:02:11,005 --> 01:02:11,546
Yes.

612
01:02:12,213 --> 01:02:13,755
It's source must be somewhere around here.

613
01:02:14,088 --> 01:02:16,046
Let's go, search for it. Come.
- Okay.

614
01:03:09,505 --> 01:03:10,130
Didn't I tell you?

615
01:03:32,796 --> 01:03:33,671
Where are you going?

616
01:03:34,088 --> 01:03:36,963
Didn't I tell you it's dangerous to go outside this area?

617
01:03:37,338 --> 01:03:41,171
Acting like a genius, you challenged us that you'd
show us ghosts in three days.

618
01:03:41,546 --> 01:03:44,296
Is this the way you chose to scare us?

619
01:03:44,296 --> 01:03:45,046
What happened?

620
01:03:45,255 --> 01:03:49,755
We thought... you were smart and would use
some new method to scare us...

621
01:03:50,255 --> 01:03:55,088
But we didn't expect you to mix mind-altering drugs
in that incense like these ordinary third-rate babas.

622
01:03:55,171 --> 01:03:56,088
Drugs?

623
01:03:56,213 --> 01:03:58,005
Then what's that incense setup in the house?

624
01:03:59,171 --> 01:04:00,005
That?

625
01:04:00,171 --> 01:04:05,005
It's a 'Homam' (fire ritual) performed
with a pure heart to the God of Destruction,

626
01:04:05,005 --> 01:04:06,921
so that you wouldn't be harmed by the evil forces here.

627
01:04:07,421 --> 01:04:09,963
What was used in it is only
pure 'Sambrani' (incense resin).

628
01:04:10,046 --> 01:04:10,671
A lie.

629
01:04:10,963 --> 01:04:13,213
If you didn't mix anything in it,

630
01:04:13,213 --> 01:04:16,088
why would everyone here get
hallucinations at the same time?

631
01:04:18,671 --> 01:04:21,630
Time itself will answer the question you've asked.

632
01:04:21,630 --> 01:04:22,213
Look.

633
01:04:22,880 --> 01:04:23,838
You're an educated person.

634
01:04:24,046 --> 01:04:28,005
We all accepted your challenge
thinking you would prove something in these three days.

635
01:04:28,171 --> 01:04:30,713
But you too played cheap tricks like all the other babas.

636
01:04:30,963 --> 01:04:33,880
Staying here even for
a moment is like degrading ourselves.

637
01:04:35,630 --> 01:04:38,630
I am saying that it is merely sacred incense.

638
01:04:39,546 --> 01:04:42,963
But you are of the opinion that I mixed something in it.

639
01:04:44,005 --> 01:04:49,338
Opinions are proven only after they travel with time...
Whether they are lies or truths.

640
01:04:49,338 --> 01:04:52,755
But you are already accepting
defeat out of fear and running away.

641
01:04:52,755 --> 01:04:53,213
Fear?

642
01:04:53,963 --> 01:04:54,463
Yes.

643
01:04:55,213 --> 01:05:02,463
Whether you believe it or not,
all of this was just an attempt I made for your protection.

644
01:05:02,505 --> 01:05:05,755
Oh, you did all this for our protection?

645
01:05:06,546 --> 01:05:07,213
Great.

646
01:05:07,338 --> 01:05:07,963
Okay.

647
01:05:08,671 --> 01:05:11,713
Then, whatever you did for our protection,
remove all of it.

648
01:05:12,630 --> 01:05:15,213
We'll see for ourselves if we can protect ourselves or not.

649
01:05:15,463 --> 01:05:17,963
If you're okay with this,
we'll spend another two days here.

650
01:05:18,005 --> 01:05:20,963
In that case, are you thinking
your plan won't work out?

651
01:05:21,380 --> 01:05:26,338
What I'm thinking about is the disasters
that are about to happen to you.

652
01:05:26,463 --> 01:05:27,588
Enough with all these words.

653
01:05:28,171 --> 01:05:29,838
If our conditions are okay with you, tell us.

654
01:05:30,130 --> 01:05:31,671
Otherwise, admit that you've lost.

655
01:05:39,046 --> 01:05:39,880
Swami!

656
01:05:42,130 --> 01:05:44,171
Remove those things.

657
01:06:00,713 --> 01:06:04,463
Who am I to stop what's destined to happen?

658
01:07:00,630 --> 01:07:02,630
Wow, isn't the place amazing?

659
01:07:02,713 --> 01:07:07,046
That idiot... Sorry, if we'd listened to that ascetic
and not come out, we would have missed it.

660
01:07:07,505 --> 01:07:08,338
Look there.

661
01:07:09,088 --> 01:07:12,880
If we go up that hill, set up a camp
and have a picnic, it would be...

662
01:07:13,921 --> 01:07:16,463
After this is over, we should
go chill for two or three days.

663
01:07:16,630 --> 01:07:20,463
But I didn't expect you to get so dull over such a small thing.

664
01:07:20,963 --> 01:07:21,755
What happened to you?

665
01:07:22,546 --> 01:07:23,255
Aparna...

666
01:07:25,421 --> 01:07:26,171
Hey, you!

667
01:07:26,671 --> 01:07:28,005
Aparna!

668
01:07:28,671 --> 01:07:30,713
If you don't remember, I'll smash you.

669
01:07:32,130 --> 01:07:32,630
Aparna!

670
01:07:33,588 --> 01:07:35,505
Why are you getting scared like a little kid?

671
01:07:35,713 --> 01:07:38,838
If you stay like this for a little longer,
you'll turn everyone into someone like you.

672
01:07:42,255 --> 01:07:43,796
How cute is this!

673
01:08:06,463 --> 01:08:07,255
What's that?

674
01:08:33,380 --> 01:08:34,588
Aparna!
- Aparna!

675
01:08:35,005 --> 01:08:36,088
Stop!
- Aparna!

676
01:08:36,755 --> 01:08:37,255
Aparna!

677
01:08:37,380 --> 01:08:38,046
What's with her?

678
01:08:39,005 --> 01:08:39,838
Hey, Aparna!

679
01:08:55,463 --> 01:08:55,921
Let's go!

680
01:09:34,338 --> 01:09:35,171
Kalyan!

681
01:10:02,130 --> 01:10:02,671
Apar...

682
01:10:03,046 --> 01:10:03,505
Apar...

683
01:10:03,838 --> 01:10:04,380
Aparna!

684
01:11:52,088 --> 01:11:53,088
My dear child...

685
01:12:25,921 --> 01:12:27,796
My dear... My dear child...

686
01:12:28,421 --> 01:12:32,171
I'm your mother.

687
01:12:35,421 --> 01:12:35,963
Hey!

688
01:12:38,880 --> 01:12:39,421
Who the hell are you?

689
01:12:41,588 --> 01:12:42,963
Who the hell are you?

690
01:12:43,130 --> 01:12:45,171
Hey, get out... leave him, you!
You leave him!

691
01:12:45,755 --> 01:12:46,838
Hey, you leave him!

692
01:12:46,838 --> 01:12:48,463
I'm telling you to leave him... leave him!

693
01:12:49,505 --> 01:12:51,713
Leave him!
Hey, you leave him!

694
01:12:52,880 --> 01:12:53,588
Leave him!

695
01:12:56,255 --> 01:12:56,921
Let go!

696
01:12:57,546 --> 01:12:58,921
Hey, let go!

697
01:12:59,463 --> 01:13:00,088
Leave him!

698
01:13:00,505 --> 01:13:01,130
Leave him!

699
01:13:01,588 --> 01:13:02,255
Leave him!

700
01:13:02,296 --> 01:13:03,546
Who the hell are you here?

701
01:13:03,713 --> 01:13:05,505
Hey, I'm telling you to let go!
Who are you?

702
01:13:06,505 --> 01:13:07,380
Who are you?

703
01:13:08,005 --> 01:13:08,963
Leave him!

704
01:13:09,296 --> 01:13:10,171
What's with you?

705
01:13:10,630 --> 01:13:11,588
Leave my kid.

706
01:13:11,755 --> 01:13:12,630
Let go of him.

707
01:13:12,755 --> 01:13:14,005
Let go of him.

708
01:13:14,588 --> 01:13:15,296
Let go!

709
01:13:15,463 --> 01:13:16,505
Let go of him.

710
01:13:16,588 --> 01:13:17,213
Hey!

711
01:13:17,671 --> 01:13:18,880
Let go of him.

712
01:13:21,880 --> 01:13:22,505
Let go of him.

713
01:13:22,546 --> 01:13:23,713
Let go of him.

714
01:13:24,171 --> 01:13:25,463
Let go of my kid.

715
01:13:25,505 --> 01:13:26,296
Let go!

716
01:13:30,171 --> 01:13:30,838
Let go!

717
01:13:33,130 --> 01:13:34,755
Will you go from here or not?
- Leave!

718
01:13:35,755 --> 01:13:36,588
Hit him.

719
01:13:40,796 --> 01:13:41,880
Will you leave or not?

720
01:13:43,296 --> 01:13:44,130
Push him away!

721
01:13:44,796 --> 01:13:45,796
Push him.
- Don't leave him.

722
01:13:48,880 --> 01:13:49,713
Go away!

723
01:14:36,546 --> 01:14:37,713
Where were you for so long?

724
01:14:39,338 --> 01:14:40,838
Vinay, let's leave this place right now.

725
01:14:41,380 --> 01:14:42,255
Come on!

726
01:14:44,546 --> 01:14:45,380
Where to?

727
01:14:45,796 --> 01:14:47,255
What do you mean where to? Home!

728
01:14:47,671 --> 01:14:50,171
It's just one more day.
We can all leave together tomorrow.

729
01:14:50,296 --> 01:14:51,838
Hey, are you crazy?

730
01:14:52,046 --> 01:14:55,671
With all this happening right before our eyes,
why do you want to stay here like a madman?

731
01:14:56,505 --> 01:14:58,421
I can't take it for another second, Vinay.

732
01:14:59,088 --> 01:15:00,171
I am leaving.

733
01:15:04,755 --> 01:15:07,088
Aparna, listen to what I'm saying.

734
01:15:07,296 --> 01:15:08,713
What will you say? What?

735
01:15:09,255 --> 01:15:11,338
Aparna, it's not what you think.

736
01:15:12,713 --> 01:15:14,171
This is all a trap set by that holy man.

737
01:15:14,338 --> 01:15:16,505
Hey, are you mad?
What do you mean a trap?

738
01:15:16,671 --> 01:15:18,463
Okay, let's assume it's a trap.

739
01:15:18,463 --> 01:15:21,130
The things happening here, that sky...
let's say it's all a trap.

740
01:15:21,505 --> 01:15:24,255
But right before our eyes, a lamb died.

741
01:15:24,380 --> 01:15:28,588
How horribly the other sheep were bleating?
You all saw it! Is that a trap too?

742
01:15:29,005 --> 01:15:30,796
Aparna, listen to me.

743
01:15:31,505 --> 01:15:32,880
It's just one more day left.

744
01:15:33,046 --> 01:15:36,338
Are you really our Nayna?
For some reason, I'm suspicious of you.

745
01:15:36,588 --> 01:15:41,755
You've been possessed by a ghost. That's why, despite all this,
you're foolishly staying here and planning to harm us.

746
01:15:41,838 --> 01:15:45,421
Hey, Aparna, we'll leave in the morning.
How can we leave in this darkness, tell me?

747
01:15:45,588 --> 01:15:47,630
It's just one night.
We'll leave by morning.

748
01:15:47,713 --> 01:15:50,005
Is there any guarantee that
nothing will happen if we stay here till morning?

749
01:15:52,463 --> 01:15:55,963
Vinay, I'm asking you for the last time.
Are you coming with me or not?

750
01:16:11,546 --> 01:16:12,046
Aparna!

751
01:16:12,088 --> 01:16:12,630
Aparna!

752
01:16:13,255 --> 01:16:14,296
Please listen to me, Aparna!

753
01:16:14,296 --> 01:16:15,338
Aparna, wait, Aparna!

754
01:16:16,338 --> 01:16:17,171
Listen to my words!

755
01:16:18,546 --> 01:16:19,255
Aparna!

756
01:18:23,463 --> 01:18:24,588
Come, come, let's go.

757
01:18:24,671 --> 01:18:25,796
Let's go.

758
01:18:39,255 --> 01:18:40,338
Let's go, let's go.

759
01:19:05,630 --> 01:19:09,380
You all go ahead. I will take her. Go.

760
01:19:09,630 --> 01:19:10,963
Come, let's go.

761
01:20:09,963 --> 01:20:12,713
My lovely son!

762
01:21:35,921 --> 01:21:37,796
Go, go! Let's go!

763
01:21:40,213 --> 01:21:41,505
He's coming! Let's go!

764
01:21:41,963 --> 01:21:43,213
You go ahead! Be careful!

765
01:22:01,671 --> 01:22:07,171
The one who attacked us at the ashram that day...
It was him, right?

766
01:22:07,713 --> 01:22:08,671
Who is he?

767
01:22:12,963 --> 01:22:15,005
IT's not him, it's her.

768
01:22:16,713 --> 01:22:18,005
She? A woman?

769
01:22:19,088 --> 01:22:20,921
Yes. Punyavati.

770
01:22:24,380 --> 01:22:30,421
Yesterday, on your way to my ashram,
you unknowingly caused an accident.

771
01:22:31,755 --> 01:22:38,963
At that time, a woman named Punyavati, who was
happily riding on a bike with her husband and son...

772
01:22:39,921 --> 01:22:41,963
died in that accident.

773
01:22:49,713 --> 01:22:53,546
Punyavati's spirit is inside him.

774
01:22:54,463 --> 01:23:02,713
She wants to take revenge on you, who caused
her death and separated her from her family.

775
01:23:03,838 --> 01:23:07,796
So a woman died because of us.
And that's why her spirit is inside him.

776
01:23:08,088 --> 01:23:11,796
You've created a super story!
And you made him act so well!

777
01:23:12,546 --> 01:23:19,296
Your story, his acting, the training you gave him...
Wow! No amount of credit is enough.

778
01:23:19,713 --> 01:23:21,005
Really, hats off to you.

779
01:23:21,588 --> 01:23:23,546
For a moment, I was genuinely scared.

780
01:23:24,796 --> 01:23:35,380
So, you think after seeing all this, we'll believe in spirits,
bow at your feet, admit our mistake, accept defeat, and just leave?

781
01:23:36,630 --> 01:23:39,046
But you missed a small logic.

782
01:23:39,796 --> 01:23:45,713
We are not some uneducated fools to
believe all this, get scared, and run away.

783
01:23:46,421 --> 01:23:47,880
This plan has failed anyway.

784
01:23:47,963 --> 01:23:50,380
You'll need some other plans for tomorrow, won't you?

785
01:23:51,130 --> 01:23:52,713
You may leave. Go think about it.

786
01:23:53,213 --> 01:23:54,630
It's getting late, right? Go.

787
01:23:55,046 --> 01:23:56,630
Come with a new plan tomorrow.

788
01:23:59,505 --> 01:24:00,671
Come. Let's go.

789
01:24:41,880 --> 01:24:44,588
Who are you? Don't come! Don't come!

790
01:24:44,671 --> 01:24:46,255
It's me, dear... I'm your mother.

791
01:24:47,296 --> 01:24:50,088
No, no. You're not our mother.

792
01:24:50,296 --> 01:24:52,296
It's true, my child. I am your mother.

793
01:24:52,380 --> 01:24:57,088
Don't come! I'm scared, sister!
- Don't do anything to us!

794
01:24:57,171 --> 01:24:59,463
Sister! Don't do anything to us!

795
01:25:00,630 --> 01:25:03,296
It's gotten dark, my child.
Let's go, come on dears.

796
01:25:09,713 --> 01:25:13,088
Will you leave or not?
Go away from here, we're scared!

797
01:25:13,088 --> 01:25:14,796
Why are you scared to see your mother, dear?

798
01:25:14,921 --> 01:25:19,380
Sister... I'm scared... Sister...
- Why are you scared, my child?

799
01:25:20,505 --> 01:25:21,880
I'm your mother, aren't I?

800
01:25:22,421 --> 01:25:26,130
Come dears, let's go. I don't know who you are.
You're not our mother.

801
01:25:26,130 --> 01:25:28,463
Go! Go!
- I am your mother, dear.

802
01:25:28,796 --> 01:25:31,588
Why the fear? Come dears, let's leave.

803
01:25:34,255 --> 01:25:37,005
I'm your mother, right? Please listen to my words, dears.

804
01:25:37,088 --> 01:25:39,588
We won't come! We are scared!

805
01:25:40,005 --> 01:25:42,880
Why are you crying, dear? I'm your mother, right?

806
01:25:43,088 --> 01:25:44,463
Come, let's leave.

807
01:25:44,546 --> 01:25:49,005
It's very dark, my child. Come, we must leave.

808
01:25:49,213 --> 01:25:50,963
Please listen to me, dear.

809
01:25:51,588 --> 01:25:53,255
We shouldn't be here in the dark.

810
01:25:54,088 --> 01:25:55,213
Come, let's go.

811
01:26:45,046 --> 01:26:46,046
What happened?

812
01:26:46,796 --> 01:26:50,046
Some woman gave poison to her children
and then killed herself on the railway track.

813
01:31:01,255 --> 01:31:02,171
Hmm.

814
01:31:08,046 --> 01:31:08,963
What is it?

815
01:31:09,796 --> 01:31:12,505
At least now tell Nayana that you love her.

816
01:31:13,713 --> 01:31:14,921
What happened now?

817
01:31:18,046 --> 01:31:19,671
Don't you know what happened?

818
01:31:23,505 --> 01:31:26,171
For 20 years, it's been all about what she likes.

819
01:31:27,255 --> 01:31:29,630
Even the dress you wear is of her taste.

820
01:31:30,338 --> 01:31:35,505
Even to go on a small outing,
you check four times if she likes it or not.

821
01:31:35,796 --> 01:31:38,838
In these 20 years, do you even have a life of your own?

822
01:31:39,921 --> 01:31:40,963
Do you have your own likes?

823
01:31:43,755 --> 01:31:47,130
You love her so madly,
but you won't even tell her.

824
01:31:49,755 --> 01:31:54,463
Love might not have an expiry date,
but life does.

825
01:32:02,421 --> 01:32:05,713
If we part now, we can never meet again.

826
01:32:13,213 --> 01:32:16,546
I'm feeling very tired.

827
01:32:16,796 --> 01:32:19,463
It feels like all my energy has been drained.

828
01:34:14,338 --> 01:34:14,921
Vinay?

829
01:34:19,046 --> 01:34:19,796
Vinay?

830
01:34:35,005 --> 01:34:35,421
Hi.

831
01:34:55,963 --> 01:34:58,463
Vinay?

832
01:34:59,421 --> 01:35:00,088
Vinay?

833
01:35:09,213 --> 01:35:09,838
Vinay?

834
01:35:30,255 --> 01:35:31,046
Vinay?

835
01:35:34,130 --> 01:35:35,505
Where are you?

836
01:35:37,796 --> 01:35:40,713
What is it? You seem tense.

837
01:35:40,880 --> 01:35:41,588
What happened?

838
01:35:42,630 --> 01:35:43,088
Nothing.

839
01:35:43,713 --> 01:35:44,505
I can tell.

840
01:35:45,005 --> 01:35:45,588
Tell me what it is.

841
01:35:46,130 --> 01:35:47,046
I said it's nothing.

842
01:35:47,588 --> 01:35:48,546
Swear on me.

843
01:35:52,880 --> 01:35:53,630
You're hiding something.

844
01:35:54,130 --> 01:35:55,213
Tell me what happened.

845
01:35:57,838 --> 01:35:59,755
Okay. If you don't want to, don't tell me.

846
01:36:00,005 --> 01:36:00,588
Okay?

847
01:36:03,171 --> 01:36:03,630
Nayana?

848
01:36:14,463 --> 01:36:15,630
Tell me.

849
01:36:17,171 --> 01:36:18,046
Vinay!

850
01:36:20,963 --> 01:36:21,588
Vinay!

851
01:36:22,463 --> 01:36:24,046
Why are you sleeping here?

852
01:36:32,963 --> 01:36:33,505
Vinay!

853
01:36:37,505 --> 01:36:38,338
Vinay!

854
01:36:52,380 --> 01:36:52,880
I...

855
01:36:53,005 --> 01:36:53,921
Kalyan!

856
01:36:55,255 --> 01:36:56,505
Kalyan!

857
01:36:57,796 --> 01:36:59,213
What happened? What happened, Aparna?

858
01:36:59,838 --> 01:37:02,046
Here... Vinay... Vinay...

859
01:37:03,338 --> 01:37:05,671
Someone dragged Vinay away, Kalyan.

860
01:37:06,505 --> 01:37:07,921
Someone took Vinay away.

861
01:37:14,005 --> 01:37:15,005
Vinay!

862
01:37:15,755 --> 01:37:17,421
Vinay!

863
01:37:19,088 --> 01:37:23,546
From there... someone took Vinay away.
Someone took him.

864
01:37:23,546 --> 01:37:28,046
What do you mean someone dragged him away?
Haven't you come out of the illusion that sanyasi created?

865
01:37:28,130 --> 01:37:31,046
Hey! I'm telling you what happened right before my eyes,
why don't you believe me?

866
01:37:31,046 --> 01:37:34,713
Someone dragged Vinay away from there.

867
01:37:41,713 --> 01:37:45,088
Perhaps, that's what a spirit is.

868
01:37:46,171 --> 01:37:47,796
Spirits really exist.

869
01:37:48,546 --> 01:37:51,171
Kalyan, please do something and save Vinay.

870
01:37:51,338 --> 01:37:53,380
Aparna! Don't be stupid!

871
01:37:54,130 --> 01:37:58,088
How did you suddenly see spirits and ghosts
that haven't been seen for 25 years?

872
01:37:59,380 --> 01:38:04,255
If you can control your fear for this one day,
we will win against that sanyasi.

873
01:38:05,630 --> 01:38:06,546
Hey, are you crazy?

874
01:38:06,630 --> 01:38:08,713
I'm telling you something really took Vinay...

875
01:38:08,713 --> 01:38:11,505
and you're talking about winning and losing,
ignoring what happened here?

876
01:38:11,546 --> 01:38:16,005
Something really took Vinay.

877
01:38:22,796 --> 01:38:24,588
Vinay!

878
01:38:26,921 --> 01:38:28,505
Vinay!

879
01:38:42,130 --> 01:38:43,880
Vinay!

880
01:38:48,671 --> 01:38:51,171
Vinay!

881
01:38:57,546 --> 01:38:59,505
Vinay!

882
01:39:07,505 --> 01:39:11,296
Vinay!

883
01:39:35,213 --> 01:39:37,213
Vinay

884
01:40:24,005 --> 01:40:24,755
Aparna!

885
01:40:52,880 --> 01:40:53,380
Naina!

886
01:40:54,338 --> 01:40:55,588
Naina!
- Where are you going?

887
01:40:55,588 --> 01:40:56,130
Let's go.

888
01:41:49,338 --> 01:41:50,755
Kalyan! What happened?

889
01:41:50,755 --> 01:41:51,713
Don't say anything, come.

890
01:41:51,755 --> 01:41:52,088
Where?

891
01:42:12,130 --> 01:42:14,171
Kalyan! Where are we going?

892
01:42:14,421 --> 01:42:14,963
I don't know.

893
01:42:15,713 --> 01:42:16,255
You don't know?

894
01:42:17,005 --> 01:42:18,213
Why are we running?

895
01:42:18,255 --> 01:42:19,130
Where's Aparna?

896
01:42:19,880 --> 01:42:23,671
Aparna is gone.
I saw... I saw something drag her away.

897
01:42:23,671 --> 01:42:25,463
Something dragged her away?
What are you talking about?

898
01:42:26,171 --> 01:42:26,838
Yes, Naina.

899
01:42:27,838 --> 01:42:29,088
What Aparna said is true.

900
01:42:30,213 --> 01:42:31,213
There's something there.

901
01:42:31,755 --> 01:42:34,005
Perhaps, the same thing took Vinay too.

902
01:42:34,630 --> 01:42:35,338
It's true, Naina.

903
01:42:35,713 --> 01:42:39,088
If what you're saying is true,
we must go to Adidev from here.

904
01:42:39,421 --> 01:42:40,005
That's not it, Naina.

905
01:42:40,005 --> 01:42:45,296
He is definitely the reason for this. He's doing something.
If we confront him, he will tell the truth. Let's go.

906
01:42:45,713 --> 01:42:46,963
Hey Naina, please!

907
01:42:47,463 --> 01:42:49,088
Listen to what I'm saying, Naina, please.
- Don't say anything.

908
01:42:49,255 --> 01:42:49,796
Naina!

909
01:42:50,338 --> 01:42:52,921
Naina, you... you don't know what happened.

910
01:42:53,421 --> 01:42:54,213
Come on, Kalyan!

911
01:42:54,213 --> 01:42:55,463
Just listen to me once, Naina.

912
01:42:56,171 --> 01:42:56,963
Please, Naina.

913
01:42:58,421 --> 01:42:59,588
Please stop, Naina.

914
01:43:00,755 --> 01:43:01,338
Naina!

915
01:43:02,130 --> 01:43:02,880
Naina!

916
01:44:38,505 --> 01:44:39,213
Naina!

917
01:44:39,630 --> 01:44:40,421
Kalyan!

918
01:44:42,505 --> 01:44:43,421
Kalyan!

919
01:44:44,380 --> 01:44:45,088
Kalyan!

920
01:44:47,463 --> 01:44:48,213
Kalyan!

921
01:44:49,630 --> 01:44:51,296
Someone, please save him!

922
01:44:51,921 --> 01:44:52,713
Kalyan!

923
01:44:56,005 --> 01:44:59,005
Please, do something and save him.

924
01:44:59,588 --> 01:45:01,296
Please, do something.

925
01:45:03,671 --> 01:45:05,755
Please, do something.

926
01:45:10,380 --> 01:45:12,088
Please, save him.

927
01:45:12,796 --> 01:45:14,088
Do something.

928
01:45:19,338 --> 01:45:20,713
He's drowning.

929
01:45:20,755 --> 01:45:22,963
Do something and save him.

930
01:45:24,463 --> 01:45:26,255
Please, do something.

931
01:45:26,963 --> 01:45:27,713
Please!

932
01:45:42,796 --> 01:45:45,671
I asked you to save him, and you throw ashes, you sanyasi?

933
01:45:48,088 --> 01:45:50,130
I admit that I've lost.

934
01:45:50,755 --> 01:45:52,046
We will leave from here.

935
01:45:52,171 --> 01:45:53,546
We won't bother you again.

936
01:45:53,880 --> 01:45:55,296
I'll fall at your feet.

937
01:45:55,796 --> 01:45:57,588
Please save him.

938
01:45:58,463 --> 01:46:00,671
Please, he will die.

939
01:46:02,171 --> 01:46:04,296
He died a long time ago.

940
01:46:08,380 --> 01:46:09,338
Not just him...

941
01:46:10,588 --> 01:46:12,088
Your friends...

942
01:46:12,880 --> 01:46:14,005
You too.

943
01:46:19,171 --> 01:46:20,088
All of you...

944
01:46:20,880 --> 01:46:22,796
Died three days ago.

945
01:46:25,671 --> 01:46:26,546
No!

946
01:46:31,963 --> 01:46:33,380
Three days ago...

947
01:46:34,463 --> 01:46:36,380
on the way to our ashram...

948
01:46:36,838 --> 01:46:38,838
While trying to avoid a bike...

949
01:46:39,755 --> 01:46:41,630
You all fell into a valley.

950
01:46:55,088 --> 01:46:56,380
What is it, sanyasi?

951
01:46:56,796 --> 01:46:58,546
Are you trying to make me go crazy?

952
01:46:59,630 --> 01:47:01,005
We... from the accident...

953
01:47:01,005 --> 01:47:02,380
we escaped.

954
01:47:03,921 --> 01:47:04,463
Hey!

955
01:47:05,130 --> 01:47:06,296
She's saying sorry, right?

956
01:47:08,421 --> 01:47:09,505
Why are you being so stubborn?

957
01:47:17,171 --> 01:47:20,546
Hey! Look...

958
01:47:35,296 --> 01:47:36,463
No, my child.

959
01:47:36,963 --> 01:47:38,088
For some reason...

960
01:47:38,255 --> 01:47:40,630
God did not give you that chance.

961
01:48:05,463 --> 01:48:06,671
What's here

962
01:48:06,796 --> 01:48:09,005
is only your astral bodies.

963
01:48:11,588 --> 01:48:12,255
No!

964
01:48:13,130 --> 01:48:14,255
I don't believe it.

965
01:48:14,755 --> 01:48:16,796
Your journey in this life has ended.

966
01:48:17,421 --> 01:48:19,963
Today is the third day since you died.

967
01:48:21,671 --> 01:48:23,546
Your last rites have also begun.

968
01:48:27,296 --> 01:48:28,505
That's why...

969
01:48:29,130 --> 01:48:31,380
You are leaving one by one.

970
01:48:32,171 --> 01:48:33,380
No! I don't believe it.

971
01:48:34,421 --> 01:48:35,880
This isn't real.

972
01:48:39,880 --> 01:48:40,755
I don't believe it.

973
01:48:40,880 --> 01:48:41,671
Not just you...

974
01:48:41,671 --> 01:48:42,713
In this creation...

975
01:48:42,880 --> 01:48:46,213
No one who faces such
an unexpected, untimely death...

976
01:48:46,296 --> 01:48:47,338
can believe it.

977
01:48:47,796 --> 01:48:50,921
Until then, a person who lived happily...

978
01:48:50,921 --> 01:48:53,546
with their wife, children, relatives, and friends...

979
01:48:53,630 --> 01:48:55,755
if they suddenly face death...

980
01:48:56,005 --> 01:48:58,755
Their state will be just as terrifying.

981
01:48:59,380 --> 01:49:01,671
I don't know what bond or enmity of how many lives...

982
01:49:02,505 --> 01:49:04,880
But you died trying to save them.

983
01:49:05,963 --> 01:49:07,546
Trying to escape from you...

984
01:49:07,546 --> 01:49:09,755
Punyavathi died.

985
01:49:11,838 --> 01:49:13,255
No! No! No!

986
01:49:20,296 --> 01:49:22,421
Just because you close your eyes...

987
01:49:22,671 --> 01:49:24,046
The past doesn't disappear.

988
01:49:42,130 --> 01:49:48,463
"Shiva, Shiva, Shiva, Shankara...
Look this way just once, oh Lord."

989
01:49:48,713 --> 01:49:54,963
"This carnival of death and birth,
Is it just a game that you play?"

990
01:49:54,963 --> 01:50:01,046
"Life and death,
Are the narrative you have penned."

991
01:50:01,671 --> 01:50:07,713
"The great flood, the final doom..
the grand Poision you keep concealed."

992
01:50:08,421 --> 01:50:16,046
"A drama, all a drama...
This is your play, O Eesha (Lord)!"

993
01:50:20,421 --> 01:50:22,963
"Eesha..."

994
01:50:39,546 --> 01:50:42,296
"Eesha..."

995
01:50:44,755 --> 01:50:48,838
"Eesha..."

996
01:51:03,963 --> 01:51:10,338
"You can reign over all the realms,
You can erase all sorrows."

997
01:51:10,505 --> 01:51:16,671
"Within every soul that worships you,
You can make your divine abode."

998
01:51:17,005 --> 01:51:23,505
"You can change your forms at will,
You can weave grand illusions."

999
01:51:23,588 --> 01:51:29,755
"From those who know not right from wrong,
Do you still demand their sacrifice?"

1000
01:51:30,171 --> 01:51:35,588
"Why do you reveal
These divine plays (leelas) of yours?"

1001
01:51:36,546 --> 01:51:42,088
"And wherever I look,
I see the legends of your glory."

1002
01:51:43,255 --> 01:51:50,421
"A drama, all a drama...
This is your play, O Eesha!"

1003
01:51:55,588 --> 01:51:57,630
"Eesha..."

1004
01:52:02,505 --> 01:52:05,505
"Eesha..."

1005
01:52:11,296 --> 01:52:13,338
Do spirits really exist?

1006
01:52:13,463 --> 01:52:14,671
This is all nonsense.

1007
01:52:14,755 --> 01:52:17,296
These old folks, with nothing to do at home...

1008
01:52:17,296 --> 01:52:19,380
talk about such things

1009
01:52:19,380 --> 01:52:22,380
and roam from house to house, that's all.

1010
01:52:22,380 --> 01:52:24,630
Don't even think about it.

1011
01:52:24,713 --> 01:52:26,796
Spirits and all that stuff is trash.

1012
01:52:26,880 --> 01:52:29,546
Dont know, i scared so much

1013
01:52:56,546 --> 01:53:00,796
You are in a situation where you can't
understand the sudden death

1014
01:53:01,421 --> 01:53:06,421
Nature has tried to make you aware of
what happened through many events

1015
01:53:14,171 --> 01:53:16,421
I smell something like burning skin, Vinay.

1016
01:53:19,338 --> 01:53:22,130
I’m seeing an illusion… of myself already burned.

1017
01:53:29,463 --> 01:53:32,213
My dear.. Please listen to my words, dears.

1018
01:53:32,296 --> 01:53:34,088
We won't come! We are scared!

1019
01:53:54,255 --> 01:53:57,713
Why do you think I kept you in this house
for three days?

1020
01:53:57,963 --> 01:54:00,713
Like lost children, you came to me.

1021
01:54:01,046 --> 01:54:05,505
So that in these three days,
I could gradually reveal the tragedy that happened

1022
01:54:05,713 --> 01:54:08,713
And give you a peaceful departure.

1023
01:54:13,963 --> 01:54:20,296
But with hatred and anger towards me,
you couldn't understand me.

1024
01:54:22,588 --> 01:54:26,005
I feel like seeing my mom and sister.

1025
01:54:26,213 --> 01:54:31,380
(Chanting)

1026
01:54:42,671 --> 01:54:48,005
(Chanting)

1027
01:55:05,505 --> 01:55:09,880
(Chanting)

1028
01:55:16,838 --> 01:55:18,505
How mysterious is God's play?

1029
01:55:20,546 --> 01:55:22,213
There are no such things as spirits,

1030
01:55:22,380 --> 01:55:24,088
and to prove that, you came here.

1031
01:55:24,880 --> 01:55:26,463
And this happened to you.

1032
01:55:26,505 --> 01:55:30,130
(Chanting)

1033
01:55:32,088 --> 01:55:33,255
You have to leave, my child.

1034
01:55:34,630 --> 01:55:36,463
Earth belongs to the living ones.

1035
01:55:37,380 --> 01:55:38,671
Not for the dead ones.

1036
01:55:41,921 --> 01:55:43,921
Even Rama and Krishna couldn't escape it.

1037
01:55:43,921 --> 01:55:45,463
Ending their incarnations and
giving up the physical body.

1038
01:55:46,546 --> 01:55:48,421
Whether it's a revered one or a commoner,

1039
01:55:49,421 --> 01:55:51,713
Nature follows the same law.

1040
01:55:51,796 --> 01:55:53,796
(Chanting)

1041
01:55:53,796 --> 01:55:55,630
When we don't accept our death...

1042
01:55:56,505 --> 01:56:00,171
Death appears to be haunting us terrifyingly.

1043
01:56:12,171 --> 01:56:14,088
If we accept and depart peacefully...

1044
01:56:15,005 --> 01:56:20,046
That same death becomes like
an angel and takes us away.

1045
01:56:21,713 --> 01:56:23,255
Depart peacefully, my child.

1046
